name: Route 66

reviews.review_text:
We stopped at Route 66 for a very late lunch after looking up the restaurant on Google. Since it was an odd hour it was sparse with just one other group. I was quite impressed by the striking interiors and artwork to reflect the pan-American cuisine. The space is open and inviting with the dining furniture comprising solid tables and chairs as well as diner style booths.
The staff was courteous and accommodating. We had dietary restrictions and the chef was able to conform to our requests. The food quality and taste was not compromised. Our custom order thin crust vegan pizza was a winner!
The cocktails are amazing.
A special shout out to Chetana for ensuring our experience was enjoyable!

Theme and ambience were good but the seats seamed like they weren't cleaned in a long time and had dust all over it.
They have very limited options for chicken lovers but they do give an option of replacing the patty with a chicken one, so that's good. We ordered the Route 66 burger and Veg primavera pizza - both of which were amazing. Price was on the higher side though.
The cocktails were poorly made with bad taste. Not worth the price at all.
Won't recommend this place for drinks but only for the food.

Went to Route 66 after a spade of years. They used to be known for their hamburgers and steaks. The decor is bit confusing between a pop-rock and Texan style and bit dated looking. However the 90s music was really nice. The hamburgers luckily were still the old style way and they had not lost their touch here. Served typically with a knife to cut the hamburger. Had the chicken roxette, pork fat boy and beef route 66 special served with old style coke bottles.

description:
### Route 66: A Culinary Road Trip Through Goa

Nestled in the vibrant heart of Goa, **Route 66** beckons diners with an inviting atmosphere and an impressive rating of **4.3** stars, based on **1,932 reviews**. As a culinary hotspot, it features several standout tags—**ambience**, **cheesecake**, **café**, and **nachos**—all of which reflect customers’ passion for this place renowned for its pan-American fare and eclectic vibe.

#### Ambiance & Design

Upon entering Route 66, guests are greeted by a lively and engaging ambiance that seamlessly blends pop-rock aesthetics with Texan charm. The décor is striking, filled with colorful artwork and murals that pay homage to American culture. The spacious layout includes solid tables, comfy chairs, and vintage diner-style booths, all contributing to an open and inviting dining room. A glance through the customer-provided photos reveals warm lighting that enhances the overall experience, along with music from the 90s that evokes nostalgia and comfort. However, some reviews mentioned the need for a thorough cleaning of the seating as there were speculations about dust accumulation.

![Route 66 Ambiance](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/geougc-cs/AHRlGdmLRjSxuTsFqCYCk07o3ROcwH4QvvG839pF06popQ3qdLjuNHg8bNe9ahTeZBX4zGeem4ADOTaDk7guPZfB87X8zJTOaCBiV6wgHUck0Nn8EWApnpdiYfVh3ZOV93qg1Zp2y7kI=w375-h281-p)

#### Menu & Culinary Experience

The menu at Route 66 is a delightful exploration of flavors, prominently featuring dishes that have become crowd favorites over the years. Signature offerings include the **Route 66 burger** and the **Veg primavera pizza**, both praised for their remarkable taste and quality. Not to be overshadowed, the **cheesecake** has also earned accolades, with many guests raving about its creamy texture. For those with dietary restrictions, the accommodating staff and chef have crafted custom orders, such as a thin crust vegan pizza, ensuring that everyone can indulge without compromise.

The thoughtful presentation of each dish reflects the care put into the culinary experience, with a visual appeal that often captivates diners. The cocktails, however, garnered mixed reviews—while some raved about their innovative blends, others found them lacking in flavor.

![Route 66 Signatures](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/geougc-cs/AHRlGdniPSFW0FEJ02lVQ74A8nmpvzEDUW54rh10A0FHk7hwfEq8JNfML8vpBKumrobzgGf5y0Fhh9O8NqfQL-rB0mVR9h8AIpKJYjb04clWd4Vmnfsk2bRt17NjVs_QzbNa8Iy1OcZ8=w375-h281-p)

#### Customer Experience & Service

Diners frequently praise the staff's friendliness and their attentiveness, contributing to a positive dining experience. Many note that the team, particularly a staff member named Chetana, goes above and beyond to ensure guests feel welcome and satisfied. The restaurant has systems in place for catering to special dietary needs, enhancing its reputation as a thoughtful and inclusive establishment. While there were some mentions of inconsistency—such as the state of the seating and variability in cocktail quality—the overall service is often described as accommodating and efficient.

#### Popularity & Reviews

The buzz surrounding Route 66 is palpable, as patrons frequently hail it as a must-visit destination in Goa. With a solid rating and a substantial number of reviews, customer sentiment leans positively, especially towards the culinary offerings. Notably, the restaurant is renowned for its hamburgers and steaks, a classic reminder of its foundations adorned with a touch of Texan flair.

#### Utilizing Visual Content

The accompanying customer photos play a vital role in illustrating the Route 66 experience. From vibrant dishes captured in full color to glimpses of the unique interiors, these snapshots provide a comprehensive visual narrative that complements the reviews. The striking contrast of the food against the backdrop of the restaurant’s eclectic decor captures the essence of what makes Route 66 a memorable locale.

In conclusion, Route 66 stands as a culinary gem within Goa, inviting food enthusiasts to experience its American-inspired menu and vibrant atmosphere. Whether you're coming for the flavorful dishes or just to soak in the unique vibe, this restaurant promises an unforgettable dining adventure.
